        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-05-25T10:02:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-05-25T10:02:00-05:00" n="107"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <head>107. Telegram From the Embassy in the Soviet Union to the Department of
                        State<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d107fn1">Source: National Archives,
                        RG 59, Central Foreign Policy File, [no film number]. Secret; Immediate.
                        Sent via the <gloss target="#t_SY_1">SY</gloss> channel.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Moscow</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-05-25T15:02:00+00:00">May 25, 1978, 1502Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11720. Subject: Technical Penetration of <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss>
                    Embassy Moscow. Ref: (A) Moscow 11684, (B) Moscow 11713.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d107fn2">See <ref target="#d106">Document 106</ref> and <ref
                            target="#d106fn2">footnote 2</ref> thereto.</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. We have entered the chimney and found a tunnel at the bottom. Tunnel heads 30
                    feet north and then turns west. Hatch entrance appears to enter Soviet changing
                    room in Embassy.</p>
                <p>2. Listening post located at bottom of shaft with headset and microphone. Line
                    box with 8 dual pin jacks also found. Headset plugged in and appears dead.</p>
                <p>3. We will enter tunnel at this time.</p>
                <p>4. Still possible that opposition has not been alerted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Matlock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
